<subSubSection id="336B350493FD4004AFF0EFF3B6B7663E" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="E383BF98754E370B0C24B0E5327DC147" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="700E3EAD1C2FDC25EC018B2DCFF3CDA9" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">
<taxonomicName id="76B707F96EFDF049ACF94F115F3B7CBF" authorityName="K. W. Xu &amp; G. L. Xu" authorityYear="2022" class="Polypodiopsida" family="Aspleniaceae" genus="Asplenium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Asplenium jiulianshanense" order="Polypodiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jiulianshanense">
<emphasis id="45B6D20CCC966E3DD64289DC76085701" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">Asplenium jiulianshanense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
somewhat resembles 
<taxonomicName id="3E152F11A84A36E06FCA7C76A57C7589" genus="A." lsidName="A. kiangsuense" pageId="0" pageNumber="113" rank="species" species="kiangsuense">
<emphasis id="423DD7D2E7F1677ED9F046903DF9D31D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="113">A. kiangsuense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its small size, rachises adaxially without a deep furrow, pinnae elliptic to trapeziform-oblong, sori 3-4 per pinna in the middle part of frond. However, the former has rachises with only one gemma near apex, pinnae (15-)20-35 pairs, pinna margins entire to sparsely crenate, exospore length 37-43 
<normalizedToken id="FCED0B0867AA065706294F4D9B54EE20" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, while the latter has rachises without gemmae near the apex, pinnae 8-20(-22) pairs, pinna margins entire to sinuate, exospore length 31-36 
<normalizedToken id="BD182BC95FC39B15A1E43D634B2C823A" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
